The paper deals with optimizing cache content placement in a wireless small cell base station, which is a problem related to network optimization and information theory. Therefore, cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) and cs.IT (Information Theory) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also proposes algorithms for cache content placement based on learning and optimization, which falls under the category of machine learning and data science, hence cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also a likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the impact of system parameters on the performance of the proposed algorithms, which is related to control systems and optimization, hence cs.SY (Systems and Control) is another likely sub-category. Finally, the paper uses numerical simulations to study the performance of the proposed algorithms, which is related to statistical learning and inference, hence cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also a likely sub-category.
